<hl>
<seg id=1> Guangxi used 15 million US dollars to build up infrastructures such as transportation and water transport </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Nanning, March 14th , by Hankui Lu - According to the report of the transportation department in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, up to the present, Guangxi has used 15 million US dollars from the World Bank, Asian Bank and loans from the Holland government and Korean government to build up infrastructures such as transportation and water transport. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In the past several years, construction of a passageway through Guangxi to the ocean has experienced speeded up construction in the big southwest region of China. </seg>
<seg id=4> In order to solve the problem of capital shortages, and increase the level of opening up policies to outside sources, Guangxi has vigorously introduced foreign funds. </seg>
<seg id=5> With total investments of 200 billion Yuan RMB, the second stage of Xijiang's pivotal shipping project used 80,000,000 US dollars loaned by the World Bank. At present, 80% of the major construction and 50% of concrete pouring has been completed. </seg>
<seg id=6> The second stage of Fangchenggang city project (from Qingzhou City to the freeway of Fangchenggang city), utilized 52,000,000 US dollars loaned by the Asian Development Bank. It is predicted that the freeway will be completed and open to use in the second half of this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> Beihaigang corollary equipment construction project used 10,000,000 US dollars loaned by the Korean government. </seg>
<seg id=8> Qinzhougang corollary equipment constructive project used 13,000,000 US dollars loaned by the Holland government. </seg>
<seg id=9> All these construction projects are proceeding smoothly. </seg>
</p>
